### Counter-Rotating Pendulum

Square swings left, tilts *right*. Position and rotation are π out of phase.

```scheme
(define (counter-x t)
  (* 60 (sin (* t 2))))

(define (counter-angle t)
  (* 0.5 (sin (+ (* t 2) 3.14))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (square 25 \"navy\")
      (transform
        (at (counter-x (elapsed)) 0)
        (angle (counter-angle (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Navy square swinging, but when it moves left it tilts right, and vice versa—a mechanical opposition.]

---


### Spring Chain (Two Disks, Lagged Phase)

Two disks oscillating vertically. The second follows the first with a time delay.

```scheme
(define (leader-y t)
  (* 40 (sin (* t 3))))

(define (follower-y t)
  (* 40 (sin (* (- t 0.3) 3))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"orange\")
      (transform
        (at -20 (leader-y (elapsed)))))
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"yellow\")
      (transform
        (at 20 (follower-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Orange disk bouncing up-down; yellow disk echoes the motion a fraction of a second later, like two weights on a shared spring.]

---


### Three-Disk Wave

Three disks in a row, each offset by a fixed phase. A traveling wave.

```scheme
(define (wave-y t phase)
  (* 30 (sin (+ (* t 4) phase))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"red\")
      (transform
        (at -40 (wave-y (elapsed) 0))))
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"green\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (wave-y (elapsed) 2.09))))
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"blue\")
      (transform
        (at 40 (wave-y (elapsed) 4.19))))))
```

[VISUAL: Red, green, and blue disks arranged horizontally, bobbing in sequence—red peaks as green dips, blue peaks as red dips, a rolling wave.]

---


### Damped Spring with Rebound Overshoot

More realistic spring: damping that allows one or two visible bounces before settling.

```scheme
(define (spring-rebound t)
  (* 70
     (exp (* -0.8 t))
     (sin (* t 8))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 12 \"salmon\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (spring-rebound (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Salmon disk bouncing vertically with two clear overshoots, then rapidly converging to rest—a tuned spring.]

---


### Critically Damped Approach

A spring tuned so it settles *without* overshooting. Fastest approach to equilibrium with no oscillation visible.

```scheme
(define (critical-damped t)
  (* 60
     (exp (* -3 t))
     (+ 1 (* 3 t))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 12 \"slate\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (critical-damped (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Slate disk smoothly gliding from an offset to the origin, no bounce, just a clean exponential slide—engineered precision.]

---


### Underdamped Spring (Visible Cycles)

Light damping. Several full swings before energy dissipates.

```scheme
(define (underdamped t)
  (* 80
     (exp (* -0.2 t))
     (sin (* t 6))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 12 \"turquoise\")
      (transform
        (at (underdamped (elapsed)) 0)))))
```

[VISUAL: Turquoise disk swinging left-right through five or six visible cycles, amplitude slowly fading—a gentle dissipation.]

---


### Overdamped Creep

Heavy damping. No oscillation at all, just a slow crawl toward equilibrium.

```scheme
(define (overdamped t)
  (* 60
     (- (exp (* -1.5 t))
        (exp (* -4 t)))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 12 \"olive\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (overdamped (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Olive disk inching from an offset to the origin with no swing—viscous, sluggish, like moving through honey.]

---


### Rotation Oscillation with Damping

A square rocking back and forth, losing angular momentum.

```scheme
(define (damped-rock t)
  (* 0.6
     (exp (* -0.4 t))
     (sin (* t 5))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (square 30 \"bronze\")
      (transform
        (angle (damped-rock (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Bronze square rocking left-right, each swing smaller, finally settling upright—a pendulum friction model.]

---


### Scale Pulse with Damping

A disk that pulses in size, the pulses shrinking until it rests at base scale.

```scheme
(define (damped-pulse t)
  (+ 1.0
     (* 0.5
        (exp (* -0.6 t))
        (sin (* t 7)))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 18 \"lavender\")
      (transform
        (scale (damped-pulse (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Lavender disk swelling and shrinking in quick pulses, each pulse fainter, until it stabilizes at 100% scale.]

