### Coupled Horizontal Oscillators (In-Phase)

Two disks side-by-side, oscillating together. They move as one.

```scheme
(define (in-phase-x t)
  (* 50 (sin (* t 3))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"cyan\")
      (transform
        (at (in-phase-x (elapsed)) -20)))
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"magenta\")
      (transform
        (at (in-phase-x (elapsed)) 20)))))
```

[VISUAL: Cyan and magenta disks swinging left-right in perfect unison, synchronized dancers.]

---


### Coupled Oscillators (Anti-Phase)

Two disks swinging in opposite directions. When one is left, the other is right.

```scheme
(define (anti-phase-x t)
  (* 50 (sin (* t 3))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"red\")
      (transform
        (at (anti-phase-x (elapsed)) -20)))
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"blue\")
      (transform
        (at (- (anti-phase-x (elapsed))) 20)))))
```

[VISUAL: Red and blue disks swinging in mirror symmetry, always moving apart or together—push-pull.]

