### Parametric Rose Curve (Polar Oscillation)

A disk tracing a polar rose. Position derived from `r = sin(k·θ)`.

```scheme
(define (rose-x t)
  (* (sin (* 3 t)) 60 (cos t)))

(define (rose-y t)
  (* (sin (* 3 t)) 60 (sin t)))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 6 \"rose\")
      (transform
        (at (rose-x (elapsed))
            (rose-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Rose disk tracing a three-petaled polar rose, a mathematical flower blooming in motion.]

