### Damped Spiral (Exponential Decay + Rotation)

A disk spiraling inward. Radius shrinks exponentially while angle increases linearly.

```scheme
(define (spiral-r t)
  (* 80 (exp (* -0.4 t))))

(define (spiral-x t)
  (* (spiral-r t) (cos (* t 3))))

(define (spiral-y t)
  (* (spiral-r t) (sin (* t 3))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"teal\")
      (transform
        (at (spiral-x (elapsed))
            (spiral-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Teal disk spiraling inward, each orbit tighter, converging on the origin—a galaxy collapse.]

