### Resonance Simulation (Driving Frequency Matches Natural Frequency)

A disk oscillating at a natural frequency. Another force (represented by growing amplitude over time) amplifies it when frequencies align.

```scheme
(define (resonance-amp t)
  (min 80 (* 20 t)))

(define (resonance-y t)
  (* (resonance-amp t)
     (sin (* t 4))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"red\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (resonance-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Red disk swinging with ever-increasing amplitude, energy building as if pushed at just the right moment each cycle—resonance runaway.]

