### Two-Body Orbit (Equal Mass, Common Center)

Two disks orbiting a shared center of mass, like a binary star.

```scheme
(define (orbit1-x t)
  (* 40 (cos (* t 2))))

(define (orbit1-y t)
  (* 40 (sin (* t 2))))

(define (orbit2-x t)
  (* -40 (cos (* t 2))))

(define (orbit2-y t)
  (* -40 (sin (* t 2))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"blue\")
      (transform
        (at (orbit1-x (elapsed))
            (orbit1-y (elapsed)))))
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"orange\")
      (transform
        (at (orbit2-x (elapsed))
            (orbit2-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Blue and orange disks orbiting in perfect opposition, always on opposite sides of the origin—a binary dance.]

