### Vertical Pendulum with Gravity Cue (Asymmetric Timing)

A disk that falls quickly and rises slowly, mimicking a pendulum under gravity. Not true physics, but perceptually weighted.

```scheme
(define (gravity-y t)
  (let ((phase (modulo t 6.28)))
    (cond
      ((< phase 3.14)
       (* -50 (sin phase)))
      (else
       (* -50 (sin (* 0.6 (- phase 3.14))))))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 12 \"maroon\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (gravity-y (elapsed)))))))
```

[VISUAL: Maroon disk swinging down fast, up slow—an asymmetric pendulum arc that *feels* heavy.]

