### Standing Wave (Three Disks, Fixed Nodes)

Three disks oscillating vertically, outer two in phase, center one in anti-phase. A standing wave pattern.

```scheme
(define (standing-y t phase)
  (* 30 (sin (+ (* t 5) phase))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"red\")
      (transform
        (at -50 (standing-y (elapsed) 0))))
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"white\")
      (transform
        (at 0 (standing-y (elapsed) 3.14))))
    (spawn
      (disk 8 \"red\")
      (transform
        (at 50 (standing-y (elapsed) 0))))))
```

[VISUAL: Two red disks on the edges moving in sync, white disk in the center moving opposite—a vibrating string's first harmonic.]

