### Coupled Oscillators with Damping (Two Disks Pulling Each Other)

Two disks oscillating, but as time passes they sync up and both damp out. A simple model of energy transfer and dissipation.

```scheme
(define (coupled-a t)
  (* 50
     (exp (* -0.2 t))
     (+ (sin (* t 3))
        (* 0.3 (sin (* t 3.2))))))

(define (coupled-b t)
  (* 50
     (exp (* -0.2 t))
     (+ (sin (* t 3.2))
        (* 0.3 (sin (* t 3))))))

(motion
  (on-wake
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"pink\")
      (transform
        (at (coupled-a (elapsed)) -20)))
    (spawn
      (disk 10 \"purple\")
      (transform
        (at (coupled-b (elapsed)) 20)))))
```

[VISUAL: Pink and purple disks swinging, initially out of sync, gradually syncing as they both lose energy—mutual damping.]

